1
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:05,320
There she is.
So small, I could reach out and...

2
00:00:05,320 --> 00:00:09,760
Crush it! Crush it! Crush it!

3
00:00:09,760 --> 00:00:12,040
Quiet, Caw!
This is my moment of destiny...

4
00:00:12,040 --> 00:00:15,000
Moment of Destiny!
Moment of destiny...

5
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:16,800
Attention armoury!

6
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:18,960
Prepare plasma cannons for firing.

7
00:00:18,960 --> 00:00:20,800
Commence countdown!

8
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:27,360
I'm the king of the world!
King of the world!

9
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:30,160
King of the world! Aaark!

10
00:00:30,160 --> 00:00:34,000
Now, forget your Bonapartes, your
Boudiceas, your Blackbeards, even...

11
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:35,320
Wha...?

12
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:38,360
This, Martha Jones, this is Baltazar.

13
00:00:38,360 --> 00:00:42,320
Scourge of the Galaxy, corsair
King of Triton on the 40th century,

14
00:00:42,320 --> 00:00:45,840
the greatest despot
that ever, ever lived!

15
00:00:45,840 --> 00:00:49,600
This is just...just...fantastic!

16
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:52,160
Yeah, it's kinda cool.
Now, the thing about Baltazar.

17
00:00:52,160 --> 00:00:56,000
Scourge of the Galaxy! Yeah...the

18
00:00:52,160 --> 00:00:56,000
most amazing thing about him is...

19
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:58,080
he forged this ship himself.

20
00:00:58,080 --> 00:01:01,040
He didn't!

21
00:00:58,080 --> 00:01:01,040
By hand. Go on, tell her, Baltazar!

22
00:01:01,040 --> 00:01:04,000
I tended her by hand,
over countless decades.

23
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,920
Burnished her into the
greatest warship in history!

24
00:01:06,920 --> 00:01:10,880
And not that long ago, blew all of
Earth's defence force from the sky.

25
00:01:10,880 --> 00:01:14,440
He really shouldn't have done that.
Shouldn't have done that!

26
00:01:14,440 --> 00:01:17,520
And now I'm going to envelop
Earth in a field of plasma fire.

27
00:01:17,520 --> 00:01:20,160
Superheat the carbonites
who crawl across its surface...

28
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:25,400
Really? So all carbon-based life
will be super-compressed in a plasma
field, making... Diamonds?!

29
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:26,960
Precisely.

30
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:30,360
Yeah, well done. Yes, every
living being turned into diamonds.

31
00:01:30,360 --> 00:01:32,200
And the plan starts in seconds!

32
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:38,160
Now, that IS a Plan.
That...is...indeed...a...plan.

33
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:41,520
Is that not the most incredible plan?

34
00:01:41,520 --> 00:01:46,040
Oh, incredible,

35
00:01:41,520 --> 00:01:46,040
but, we're gonna stop him, yeah?

36
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:46,040
Mm. By giving him...this!

37
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:49,120
Wha...? I like to stir things up.

38
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:53,360
Oooh, shouldn't have done that.

39
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:55,520
He shouldn't have broken it
because...?

40
00:01:55,520 --> 00:02:00,480
It wasn't just any old spoon.
It passed through the hands of the
greatest chefs of planet Earth.

41
00:02:02,400 --> 00:02:08,920
Fanny, Delia, Madame Cholet. It was
antique, forged by inhabitants of a
planet that specialised in Ribicola.

42
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:12,240
Fungus?

43
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:12,240
Oh, yes, but not just any old fungus.

44
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:14,760
No, a special hydroxiding fungus...

45
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:17,840
There's been no treatment for it
these last 2,000 years.

46
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:21,120
Which is why,
Baltazar, Scourge of the Galaxy...

47
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:23,200
Your deck is rusting away!
Wha...?

48
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:28,120
Nooo!

49
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:31,520
That's not ordinary rust!
Nah, I pepped it up a bit.

50
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:33,840
Gave it a bit of zing.
A bit of va-va-voom.

51
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:35,520
Va-va-voom! Va-va-voom!

52
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:38,720
Doctor, you can't leave him.
Not to the rust!

53
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:38,720
Ah well...

54
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:47,040
Will Baltazar ever get caught?

55
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:49,600
I imagine so. His luck
can't hold out forever.

56
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:55,680
So what'll happen, d'you think?
In this era? Most likely
prison planet for him would be...

57
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:56,960
Volag-Noc.

58
00:02:56,960 --> 00:03:01,360
Yeah, that's where I'd take him
if it was up to me.
Coldest place in the galaxy.

59
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:06,080
Brrrr. Nasty. Yup. Now...give
me a number between zero and 99!

60
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:08,120
45. And another!

61
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:11,640
72. Another! Three.
What is this? Galactic lottery?

62
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:18,320
Destination setting!
And you, Martha Jones, have
randomly chosen to take us to...

63
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:21,360
Copacabana Beach! Arriba!

64
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,880
I'll get you for this, Doctor!

65
00:03:28,880 --> 00:03:31,360
I'll make you
sorry you were ever born!

66
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:12,000
Yes!

67
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:15,880
670 million miles an hour, and a bit!

68
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:15,880
Rock on!

69
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:18,720
You're just a boy racer, aren't you?
Ha!

70
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:20,800
Whoah!

71
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,800
What was that - emergency stop?

72
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:25,440
Owww, search me.
There's nothing in the manual...

73
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:32,400
Go on, then. We've stopped.

74
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:42,160
I've died and gone to Bill
Oddie heaven. Bill Oddie heaven!

75
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:44,040
I know you! It's Caw, isn't it?

76
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:46,240
Welcome to Pheros, Miss Martha.

77
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:47,880
It's Caw's home.

78
00:04:47,880 --> 00:04:49,680
How're you doing, Caw?

79
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:51,720
I likes you, Miss Martha.

80
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:57,920
Oh! That's for savin' Caw's
life all them years ago.

81
00:04:57,920 --> 00:05:00,880
Thank you, Caw. It's really lovely.

82
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:02,440
Got some news for you, Doctor.

83
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:04,480
'Bout Baltazar.

84
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:06,400
Let him out of Volag-Noc.

85
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:08,280
Volag-Noc? I was right, Martha!

86
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:10,840
Yeah, great. Caw, why'd
they release him?

87
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:13,560
Say he's reformed.

88
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:18,720
But Caw reckons he's as bad as ever
he was. He'll be comin' for Caw.

89
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:22,240
Caw sold him out, for a bar of gold.

90
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:26,200
Or three...
What do you need gold for?
He eats it.

91
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:28,200
He won't rest, Doctor!

92
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:33,720
He seeks his heart's desire
and knows how to find it. He does?

93
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:35,240
The Infinite!

94
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:38,480
Oh, that's just a legend.

95
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:39,600
What is?

96
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:43,880
Baltazar thinks different.
Thinks he knows how to find it.

97
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:46,720
Find what? The Infinite.

98
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:49,360
Yeah, I got that.
But what exactly is the Infinite?

99
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:55,640
Well, let's just say there are
things out there in space, Martha,

100
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:57,880
things that pre-date our reality,

101
00:05:57,880 --> 00:06:00,920
relics from the Dark Times.

102
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:04,520
Oh, a fairy tale?
Oh, far, far more than that.

103
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:08,720
There was a time when the universe
was so much smaller than it is now...

104
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:11,960
A darker, older time of chaos.

105
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:18,720
Creatures like the Racnoss,
the Nestenes and the Great Vampyres
rampaged through the Void.

106
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:22,160
And this Infinite is one of those
"relics from the dark time"?

107
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:28,000
It's said that if anyone
were to find the Infinite,
they'd receive their heart's desire.

108
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,480
And frankly, that's
quite a thing to receive.

109
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:32,600
Yeah, but how's
Baltazar gonna find it?

110
00:06:35,880 --> 00:06:39,040
That's how.
What's that? It's a data chip.

111
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:41,880
Part of a black-box recorder.

112
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:43,880
Dark Time technology.

113
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:46,400
Baltazar gave it to me
for safekeeping.

114
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:48,000
Should be four of 'em.

115
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:50,960
You need to use each one
to find the next.

116
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:53,160
And find all four,
you find the Infinite?

117
00:06:53,160 --> 00:06:56,560
Are we going on a quest, then?
No. The Infinite stays lost.

118
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:59,280
Nothing more than a legend.

119
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:04,120
As last custodian to the Secrets
of the Universe, it's my duty
to see it stays that way.

120
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:08,720
He mustn't! Mustn't!
He's got a copy!

121
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:14,120
I can't let someone like Baltazar,
corrupt and twisted, have access
to that kind of power.

122
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:16,560
Caw, you'd better
be right about this.

123
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:25,280
Planet Bouken.

124
00:07:25,280 --> 00:07:28,880
OK. Here...we...go!

125
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:37,320
The tracker's in place?
Thank you, Caw.

126
00:07:37,320 --> 00:07:39,280
It's really lovely. Aaaark!

127
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:45,160
Then the Doctor's going to
find me the Infinite, going to
find me my heart's desire...

128
00:07:45,160 --> 00:07:50,680
Heart's desire! Heart's desire!
And then, I'll have my revenge!

129
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:53,040
Revenge! Revenge!

130
00:07:57,440 --> 00:07:59,160
Ah, Martha, see those?

131
00:07:59,160 --> 00:08:01,760
Artificial suns. Never!

132
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:04,400
Someone wanted the planet Bouken
warmed up.

133
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:09,400
What are they? Oil rigs.

134
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:13,120
Oil rigs?! Hang on.
They still need oil, in the future?

135
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:16,640
It ran out on Earth. The

136
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:16,640
corporations went drilling elsewhere.

137
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:19,200
To look at them,
you'd think they were alive.

138
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:26,120
You think?! Run? What now?

139
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:29,360
Er, well, I'm open to suggestions...

140
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:30,920
Er...

141
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:33,840
How'd you do that?

142
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:36,200
Oh, Martha, you're brilliant!

143
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:40,040
Oh, yeah, now you're just
showing off. Whoah!

144
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:51,760
Hoist the colours, Mr Mate!

145
00:08:51,760 --> 00:08:56,720
Aye aye, Captain! Let OilCorp see
that the Black Gold is in business!

146
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:58,800
Aye aye, Captain! A-harr.

147
00:09:00,920 --> 00:09:04,840
Pirates?! I'm Swabb,
First Mate aboard the Black.

148
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:09,200
Now then, Mr Mate, put her in
reverse! Aye aye, Captain! A-Harr!

149
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:13,360
You two might want to hold on tight.

150
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:15,120
To the rail? Aye aye, Captain!

151
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:17,720
Take the strain, me hearties!

152
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:19,760
Heave lads!

153
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:23,320
All right, Swabb, maximum power!
Aye!

154
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:39,240
Well, that I didn't expect.

155
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:39,240
Cut thrust, Mr Mate.

156
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:43,200
Then pull the rig in?
And siphon it, Swabb!

157
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:46,680
Hello there, Captain...? Captain
Kaliko. Hello. I'm the Doctor.

158
00:09:46,680 --> 00:09:49,320
Martha and I...
Why are they smashing the oil rigs?

159
00:09:49,320 --> 00:09:51,040
Told you, it's the 40th century.

160
00:09:51,040 --> 00:09:54,840
The oil corporations are sucking
the solar system dry to feed demand.

161
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:59,280
Petrol prices are through the roof
and the colonies that can't afford

162
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:59,280
to pay are dying.

163
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:03,400
Aye. And the oil companies
call us pirates.

164
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:06,920
So you're smashing the rigs,
siphoning off the petrol...I see.

165
00:10:06,920 --> 00:10:08,520
Robbing the rich to fuel the poor?

166
00:10:08,520 --> 00:10:11,920
But that's brilliant! What d'you
think we should do with them, Swabb?

167
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:13,680
I don't know, Cap'n.

168
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:15,200
Can't hear you!

169
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:25,000
A skeleton crew? Literally.

170
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:29,680
Less of a drain on rations.

171
00:10:29,680 --> 00:10:35,920
Now, what I reckon is, to land
up in a place like this,
you dogs're either OilCorp spies

172
00:10:35,920 --> 00:10:38,680
or planning a spot
of piratin' yourselves...

173
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:41,080
Or indeed, none of the above...

174
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:44,840
Either way, I don't want you
on the Black Gold.

175
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:50,080
So ahoy there,
me heartless hearties,
throw these sandlubbers overboard!

176
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:52,160
Yeah...ahhh...

177
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:05,440
Hold hard there, lads!

178
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:10,320
Swabb, you swab! Is this mutiny?

179
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:13,960
Yesss!
Never, Cap'n Kaliko, not mutiny!

180
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:15,840
Nooo.

181
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:19,440
I just wondered if they be OilCorp
spies, mayhaps we dispose

182
00:11:19,440 --> 00:11:23,400
of the bodies by putting them inside
one of the oil rigs? A-harr...

183
00:11:23,400 --> 00:11:26,160
Make it look like an accident?

184
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:29,960
Yer not as empty-headed
as you seems, Mr Mate!

185
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:32,560
We'll use the one
we just keelhauled!

186
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:34,240
Aye aye, Cap'n.

187
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:39,000
Don't worry, Doctor, Martha.
You're perfectly safe with me.

188
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:43,200
What's he up to? Hmmm...

189
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:48,800
I don't think our Mr Swabb is all
he's cracked up to be. I wonder...

190
00:12:02,880 --> 00:12:04,680
Said your prayers yet, Doctor?

191
00:12:04,680 --> 00:12:07,480
So, um, sorry, let me see
if I've got this right?

192
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:12,600
We somehow get inside this rig

193
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:12,600
you've drained of oil, and then what?

194
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:18,640
A quick blast from me mate
Swabb's laser pistol,
the remaining oil ignites...

195
00:12:18,640 --> 00:12:20,760
OilCorp find us dead inside.

196
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:23,560
Boiled in oil? That's murder!

197
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:25,240
Accidents happen.

198
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:27,680
Now, me hearties! The plank!

199
00:12:31,560 --> 00:12:34,840
Careful with that!
Uh-uh-uh-uh-uh...me first.

200
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:37,960
Thought Swabb would have
made his move by now.

201
00:12:37,960 --> 00:12:39,400
What move? He's no pirate.

202
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:43,280
If he thinks we're with this OilCorp,
then my guess is... That he is too?

203
00:12:43,280 --> 00:12:45,360
Yeah. Fingers crossed. Ready!

204
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:50,880
I like your style, Doctor.

205
00:12:50,880 --> 00:12:54,320
Shame you have to die!

206
00:12:50,880 --> 00:12:54,320
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

207
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:58,720
Now, let us go,
or I'll destroy your ship!

208
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:00,280
What, with that?

209
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:02,520
No deal!

210
00:13:02,520 --> 00:13:05,440
I wish you weren't so obstinate,
Kaliko. Oh, well.

211
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:08,920
Why's it not working?

212
00:13:08,920 --> 00:13:11,000
Um, patience.

213
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:14,360
Er...sand in the mechanism.

214
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:16,080
Hang on...

215
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:20,080
Success! And?

216
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:22,280
And hold on tight.

217
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:29,240
OilCorp dog!
You're damaging the Black Gold!

218
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:32,280
We're actually on your side,
Captain! We came here to save you!

219
00:13:32,280 --> 00:13:33,960
It's all right, Martha.

220
00:13:33,960 --> 00:13:37,440
The Captain's pirate days are over.
I'm with OilCorp.

221
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:42,440
Told you!

222
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:42,440
And OilCorp have promised me a new
body to replace this bag of bones.

223
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:46,000
Same goes for you, me hearties, if
you'll help me turn the Captain in!

224
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,480
They'll never turn on me!

225
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:52,680
Oh, no.

226
00:13:52,680 --> 00:13:57,760
Thing is, Captain, Swabb here seems
to think Martha and I are
with OilCorp too... You're not?

227
00:13:57,760 --> 00:14:00,560
No. You're not. No!

228
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:02,680
Captain, we've come here
to rescue you.

229
00:14:02,680 --> 00:14:04,360
Why? Doesn't matter, Captain.

230
00:14:04,360 --> 00:14:05,920
You're time is up!

231
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:08,760
Rigs! Attack!

232
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:26,080
Lucky they're not great shots!

233
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:26,080
Define "lucky"!

234
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:29,120
No! No, more precision.

235
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:31,280
Fire with more... Waaaaghhh.

236
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:35,080
Roll with it, Martha!

237
00:14:46,240 --> 00:14:47,720
Doctor?

238
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:49,200
Doctor?

239
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:52,400
Aah! Forget it, he's gone.

240
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:57,000
But at least I can think
of a good use for you.

241
00:14:54,280 --> 00:14:57,000
Oh, really! Yes.

242
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:01,760
My five year service reward
from OilCorp is that I get
to choose a new body soon.

243
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:06,720
And you know what?
I can see myself wearing yours.

244
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:08,560
Slinky, yeah!

245
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:14,200
Look, me and the Doctor aren't here
to cause you and OilCorp trouble.

246
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:17,160
We're on a dead important mission.
Gotta collect data chips.

247
00:15:17,160 --> 00:15:22,160
Stop this Baltazar stealing a big
spaceship called the Infinite,
which'll give him infinite power.

248
00:15:22,160 --> 00:15:25,240
And that's bad cos he's not
a nice bloke. Oh, and Swabb?

249
00:15:25,240 --> 00:15:27,720
Yeah? Um...behind you?

250
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:31,720
Aye-aye!

251
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:34,240
Oooh, sorry! Doctor!
Wooah...

252
00:15:41,560 --> 00:15:43,480
Will the vile dog live?

253
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:46,280
The sand seemed soft,
so it probably broke his fall.

254
00:15:46,280 --> 00:15:50,200
I'll get you for this! Yup, he's OK.

255
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:52,000
You need some help?
Could you?

256
00:15:54,040 --> 00:15:57,000
Ow, oooh! Doctor, you said
you'd come here for me.

257
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:59,480
What exactly did you mean by that?

258
00:15:59,480 --> 00:16:01,400
Ah. Well?

259
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:03,640
Your earring, Captain.

260
00:16:03,640 --> 00:16:05,680
You know what it is, really?

261
00:16:08,280 --> 00:16:12,080
You're after the Infinite? You fool!

262
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:17,960
Now, I was going offer you
both a berth on my next ship,

263
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:21,360
but seeing as you had an
ulterior motive in rescuing me...

264
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:31,680
There's only room for one
in my lifeboat, anyhow.

265
00:16:42,720 --> 00:16:45,840
Looks like she came down near
the TARDIS. We have to catch her.

266
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:48,960
If Baltazar gets that data chip,
and finds the Infinite...

267
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:51,600
He gets his heart's desire -
destruction of you, me and Earth.

268
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:03,400
Look! Aw, no.

269
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:06,040
Surely the fall couldn't do that?

270
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:08,920
No. She's been murdered.

271
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:14,080
Live by the cutlass, die by
the cutlass, it seems. Doctor?

272
00:17:14,080 --> 00:17:18,600
I'm so sorry Kaliko...but we've
got what we came for, Martha.

273
00:17:18,600 --> 00:17:20,800
Let's see where we're going next.

274
00:17:29,360 --> 00:17:35,680
Hang on! There could be anything out
there. Snakes like bendy buses,
sabre-toothed gorillas. Anything!

275
00:17:35,680 --> 00:17:42,240
Excellent! Right...that way is Main

276
00:17:35,680 --> 00:17:42,240
Street, so that's probably downtown.
Where's the lights? Lights?!

277
00:17:42,240 --> 00:17:45,760
City like this should be full
of lights, especially at night.

278
00:17:45,760 --> 00:17:48,040
INSECTS BUZZ

279
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:56,600
Doctor! They're bugs!

280
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:56,600
So I see, and they're about to swarm!

281
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:07,080
Doctor! The bugs...

282
00:18:07,080 --> 00:18:08,680
Swarming...all around us...

283
00:18:08,680 --> 00:18:11,960
Go on! Get out of it!

284
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:14,080
What's the matter with you two?

285
00:18:18,160 --> 00:18:22,160
Doctor? I know.
And what are you staring at?

286
00:18:22,160 --> 00:18:27,680
Thank you. For the timely arrival.
Mr, Um? Mergrass. Ulysees Mergrass.

287
00:18:27,680 --> 00:18:32,160
Good thing the bugs listen to you.
We have an understanding. I noticed.

288
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:36,600
I'm here to provide their community,
via their Queen, with protection.

289
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:37,960
SIREN WAILS

290
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:37,960
What's that?

291
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:40,480
What they need protecting from.

292
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:53,000
Hang on. Those are warplanes.
What do you expect in a war zone?

293
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,560
BOTH: A war zone?!

294
00:18:57,880 --> 00:19:00,800
Sonic attack! Incoming!

295
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:03,760
You know what?
I think he's got the right idea.

296
00:19:14,080 --> 00:19:16,320
Martha? Martha! Look out!

297
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:31,160
Pretty, isn't it?
If you like that sort of thing.

298
00:19:31,160 --> 00:19:34,840
Careful!
Don't touch what isn't yours. Yet.

299
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:37,320
Breakages must still be paid for.

300
00:19:37,320 --> 00:19:39,240
Besides which, they won't activate

301
00:19:39,240 --> 00:19:42,800
until I give your Queen this
keycoder to switch everything on.

302
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:48,680
You all right? Turns out the

303
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:48,680
towers are built from dung, not rock.

304
00:19:48,680 --> 00:19:50,760
But even so. Yeah, I'm fine.

305
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:58,280
It's beautiful.

306
00:19:58,280 --> 00:20:00,520
Really beautiful.

307
00:20:00,520 --> 00:20:03,160
Well said, Martha Jones.

308
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:08,560
Ah! Martha Jones, the Mantasphid
Queen; the Mantasphid Queen, Ma'am,
Martha Jones.

309
00:20:08,560 --> 00:20:10,840
Your...Majesty? Spot on.

310
00:20:10,840 --> 00:20:13,320
As I was saying,
these alien attackers...

311
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:16,520
I hope you're not putting
a business proposition, Doctor!

312
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:19,560
The bidding is over. I won.

313
00:20:19,560 --> 00:20:22,480
Mergrass is correct, Doctor.

314
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:27,200
We have our military adviser
already, we do not need another.

315
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:29,840
Oh. "Military adviser", is it?

316
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:32,960
Interesting euphemism for
gun-running. Gun-running?

317
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:34,560
In the crates.

318
00:20:38,160 --> 00:20:42,200
They've caught a pilot!
Mergrass, they've caught a pilot!

319
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:45,720
Stand well back. I want to see
what it is you're fighting against.

320
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:50,920
Oh. What are you?

321
00:20:56,720 --> 00:20:58,360
Crush it! Squash it!

322
00:20:58,360 --> 00:21:00,880
Get it away from me!
Wait, Doctor, it's...

323
00:21:00,880 --> 00:21:02,400
Trying to kill me, I know!

324
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:05,480
No! It's panicking.
Doctor, it's just frightened!

325
00:21:05,480 --> 00:21:07,080
Oh.

326
00:21:07,080 --> 00:21:09,720
Oh, oh, Martha, you're a marvel.

327
00:21:09,720 --> 00:21:12,440
Calm, calm, calm, calm.
Hey, I'm not going to hurt you.

328
00:21:17,760 --> 00:21:21,040
Thank you. Thank you so much.

329
00:21:21,040 --> 00:21:23,240
Training didn't prepare me!

330
00:21:23,240 --> 00:21:26,240
I didn't... It's all right,
it's all right, calm down.

331
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:28,280
You're fine now. Sorry.

332
00:21:28,280 --> 00:21:30,280
Suit got damaged when I came down.

333
00:21:30,280 --> 00:21:34,920
No air left. I thought I was
gonna die, I don't want to die.

334
00:21:34,920 --> 00:21:37,600
Well, you didn't. Fleshy biped!

335
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:42,080
We must be protected from
fleshy bipeds! Destroy them all!

336
00:21:42,080 --> 00:21:44,040
You can destroy them, Your Majesty.

337
00:21:44,040 --> 00:21:45,920
With the weapons you've bought.

338
00:21:45,920 --> 00:21:48,120
What's your name, pilot?
Pilot Kelvin.

339
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:50,560
Well, Pilot Kelvin,
what's wrong with you?

340
00:21:50,560 --> 00:21:54,800
Picking a fight with a
bunch of defenceless bugs?!

341
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:54,800
Eh? We didn't start it!

342
00:21:54,800 --> 00:21:56,640
Yes, they did.

343
00:21:56,640 --> 00:22:00,160
The fleshy bipeds have been trying
to exterminate us! Wipe us out!

344
00:22:00,160 --> 00:22:02,280
No! You don't understand.

345
00:22:02,280 --> 00:22:05,320
This is my er... This...
This was my home.

346
00:22:05,320 --> 00:22:07,120
Where I was born, brought up.

347
00:22:07,120 --> 00:22:09,040
We were here first!

348
00:22:09,040 --> 00:22:11,560
Is this true?

349
00:22:11,560 --> 00:22:14,160
This used to be a lovely place.

350
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:16,160
My parents had a homestead here.

351
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:20,960
Then the bugs arrived and drove the
people out. I only joined up once...

352
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:22,640
Once my parents were killed.

353
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:24,200
Killed? Why?

354
00:22:24,200 --> 00:22:26,040
Why did you attack?

355
00:22:26,040 --> 00:22:30,280
So many lovely animals
they had here.

356
00:22:30,280 --> 00:22:32,120
So much lovely dung!

357
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:34,320
You invaded this planet for dung?!

358
00:22:34,320 --> 00:22:36,920
It's one of the last
fertile planets in the galaxy.

359
00:22:36,920 --> 00:22:40,200
If it falls, there'll be a
famine like you wouldn't believe.

360
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:42,200
Your Majesty, if I may?

361
00:22:42,200 --> 00:22:43,920
My job here is done.

362
00:22:43,920 --> 00:22:47,440
I've supplied you with the
means to destroy your enemies.

363
00:22:47,440 --> 00:22:50,600
Your contract stipulates
final payment on delivery.

364
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:52,280
Did it?

365
00:22:52,280 --> 00:22:56,000
Guess what, Mergrass. I lied!

366
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:59,040
There will be no payment!

367
00:22:59,040 --> 00:23:02,680
Mantasphids don't make deals
with fleshy bipeds.

368
00:23:02,680 --> 00:23:04,080
Typical mantashpid.

369
00:23:04,080 --> 00:23:06,080
I should've listened to the others.

370
00:23:06,080 --> 00:23:09,840
What others? The prisoners.
There was a mantasphid there, too.

371
00:23:09,840 --> 00:23:14,160
Tipped me off about this little
war, so I decided to do the deal.

372
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:17,400
You were in prison? Good grief, no.

373
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:20,000
I was a broker, a dealer.

374
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:23,480
I'd get letters and gifts to
the inmates, and in return...

375
00:23:23,480 --> 00:23:25,120
You got well paid?

376
00:23:25,120 --> 00:23:27,000
Of course.

377
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:30,920
But the governor always said that
you could never trust a mantasphid.

378
00:23:30,920 --> 00:23:34,640
The Governor of which prison
was this? Volag-Noc perhaps?

379
00:23:34,640 --> 00:23:39,960
Volag-Noc? But isn't that where
Baltazar was? You know of Baltazar?

380
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:42,720
AIR-RAID SIRENS WAIL

381
00:23:42,720 --> 00:23:45,000
The fly-ships, they're coming back!

382
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:47,840
Bugs, defend us!
They'll destroy us all.

383
00:23:47,840 --> 00:23:52,320
We're going to die too unless
we get away. Forget it.
You can't get far enough away.

384
00:23:52,320 --> 00:23:56,600
Why not? Because Earth Command
can't afford to lose this planet!

385
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:58,600
You see, they'll even sacrifice me.

386
00:24:01,160 --> 00:24:03,200
Your Majesty,
there might still be a way.

387
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:05,520
Ah, Doctor.

388
00:24:05,520 --> 00:24:09,600
This is a fleshy biped thing,
is it not?

389
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:11,480
"Never say die"? Yeah, exactly!

390
00:24:11,480 --> 00:24:15,440
Fleshy bipeds are very
stupid creatures.

391
00:24:15,440 --> 00:24:17,040
But the fight goes on!

392
00:24:17,040 --> 00:24:19,080
We'll win this war yet!
Pilot Kelvin!

393
00:24:19,080 --> 00:24:25,400
What will they do to the city? Well,
the plan was spatial disintegration

394
00:24:19,080 --> 00:24:25,400
of this 100-mile vector.

395
00:24:25,400 --> 00:24:31,120
They're going to burn us
out of space and time?
Kills all known bugs. Dead.

396
00:24:37,320 --> 00:24:39,960
So we stand here
while they vaporise us?

397
00:24:39,960 --> 00:24:41,960
Mergrass, what do we do?

398
00:24:41,960 --> 00:24:45,000
- You're asking me?
- You're my military adviser!

399
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:47,520
You know tactics! You know weapons!
Help us!

400
00:24:47,520 --> 00:24:50,840
I'd have happily helped you
when I thought I was getting paid

401
00:24:50,840 --> 00:24:53,720
but without this,
the weapons are useless.

402
00:24:53,720 --> 00:24:57,240
And without my money,
you get nothing.

403
00:24:57,240 --> 00:25:02,000
Mergrass! Mergrass! Come back!

404
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:06,640
We need to keep track of Mergrass. He
has the data chip we need
to continue this treasure hunt.

405
00:25:06,640 --> 00:25:09,200
It is decided.

406
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:14,320
How do we surrender
to the fleshy bipeds?

407
00:25:14,320 --> 00:25:17,160
At last. Pilot Kelvin, have you
got a communications system?

408
00:25:17,160 --> 00:25:20,360
Inside my helmet, sir!
But it was damaged when I crashed.

409
00:25:20,360 --> 00:25:22,360
Oh, we'll soon
have that sorted.

410
00:25:22,360 --> 00:25:25,320
Hurry! Hurry! We want to surrender!

411
00:25:25,320 --> 00:25:28,680
Doctor, there's no protocol for
negotiation with the Mantasphids.

412
00:25:28,680 --> 00:25:32,760
Then make one! I can't. They invaded
our homes, killed our families.

413
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:36,040
They're also living sentient
beings that have a right to exist.

414
00:25:36,040 --> 00:25:37,800
Maybe not here, but somewhere.

415
00:25:37,800 --> 00:25:40,640
'Mantasphid hive destruction
commences in 60 seconds.'

416
00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:43,880
Oooh, that's not good.
Please, Doctor. Hurry.

417
00:25:43,880 --> 00:25:48,960
Doctor! Listen, if the bugs can't
surrender, surely we can, can't we?

418
00:25:48,960 --> 00:25:54,720
You are brilliant! Pilot, tell them
to open up a visual channel. Control!

419
00:25:54,720 --> 00:26:00,760
This is Pilot Kelvin, imperative you
open a visual link to this system.
Please respond. Roger.

420
00:26:00,760 --> 00:26:02,520
Hurry, Doctor!

421
00:26:02,520 --> 00:26:07,400
Ahoy there,
ye Earth Command nobodies!

422
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:14,680
You got Doctor Vile,
pirate o' the constellations,
givin' you a big white flag!

423
00:26:14,680 --> 00:26:18,600
Fact is, me an' me
mad mucker Martha here...

424
00:26:18,600 --> 00:26:21,200
Arr! Arr! Arr!

425
00:26:21,200 --> 00:26:23,640
Umm, no. No, don't, don't do that.

426
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:30,880
We've been rulin' over these insect
raiders, held their Queenie hostage!

427
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:33,880
But, we has to admit,
you got us beaten.

428
00:26:33,880 --> 00:26:35,480
Come on in and get us.

429
00:26:35,480 --> 00:26:41,200
We surrender! That should do it.

430
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:43,480
What have you done, Doctor?

431
00:26:43,480 --> 00:26:46,160
Taken the rap for you, Queenie.
Ended your war!

432
00:26:46,160 --> 00:26:48,400
They'll never believe it.
You reckon?

433
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:51,360
All units,
hive destruction cancelled.

434
00:26:51,360 --> 00:26:55,840
Your priority now is to apprehend
male human, codename "Doctor Vile"!

435
00:26:55,840 --> 00:27:00,040
How can we thank you, Doctor?

436
00:27:00,040 --> 00:27:05,640
Easy. Work with the humans, not
against them. Young Kelvin here

437
00:27:00,040 --> 00:27:05,640
could make a great ambassador. Me?

438
00:27:05,640 --> 00:27:08,720
Listen, Your Majesty,
the humans' farms will need power.

439
00:27:08,720 --> 00:27:12,240
Light and heat are hard to come by
in an oil-starved universe, right?

440
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:14,960
And you're naturally phosphorescent.
Think you can make a deal?

441
00:27:14,960 --> 00:27:17,880
And you'll get all the dung
you could ever want!

442
00:27:17,880 --> 00:27:20,960
Brilliant! So what's next?

443
00:27:20,960 --> 00:27:23,840
We skedaddle out of here
before Kelvin's mates arrive.

444
00:27:23,840 --> 00:27:25,360
Good luck, everyone.

445
00:27:27,600 --> 00:27:30,800
What now?
Catch up with Mergrass and go?

446
00:27:30,800 --> 00:27:32,800
Oh, we've found him.

447
00:27:32,800 --> 00:27:35,160
Oh, no! No!

448
00:27:35,160 --> 00:27:37,000
Sudden dehydration.

449
00:27:42,840 --> 00:27:45,960
Take the data chip, and let's go.

450
00:27:42,840 --> 00:27:45,960
We can't just leave him!

451
00:27:45,960 --> 00:27:49,040
It's like Captain Kaliko
all over again. Isn't it just.

452
00:27:49,040 --> 00:27:50,640
But Martha, we can't stay!

453
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:52,880
We're criminals, remember?

454
00:27:56,640 --> 00:27:58,360
Next data chip located!

455
00:27:58,360 --> 00:28:00,840
It's... Ah. It's... Oooh.

456
00:28:00,840 --> 00:28:03,720
Where? Is it bad?
You wearing thermals?

457
00:28:06,400 --> 00:28:08,560
Come on, you.

458
00:28:08,560 --> 00:28:10,280
Where are we going?

459
00:28:10,280 --> 00:28:11,880
Where are we, full stop!

460
00:28:11,880 --> 00:28:15,520
Well, we've now met two people
from the prison on Volag-Noc, right?

461
00:28:15,520 --> 00:28:18,320
Right, but there's no prison here!

462
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:20,800
You were saying?

463
00:28:20,800 --> 00:28:22,440
Doctor!

464
00:28:25,120 --> 00:28:27,320
I thought you'd never get here!

465
00:28:29,120 --> 00:28:30,640
Er, we're visitors.

466
00:28:30,640 --> 00:28:32,880
Visitors, mind! Oi!

467
00:28:32,880 --> 00:28:36,000
This item is confiscated.

468
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:40,080
What? Scanning for malfeasance.

469
00:28:40,080 --> 00:28:45,360
No convictions. No confirmation of
criminal activity. Well, obviously.

470
00:28:45,360 --> 00:28:47,840
Scanning.

471
00:28:47,840 --> 00:28:50,760
3,005 outstanding convictions...

472
00:28:50,760 --> 00:28:55,320
That many? ..With 6,000 more to be

473
00:28:50,760 --> 00:28:55,320
taken into consideration. Doctor?

474
00:28:55,320 --> 00:28:58,080
It's an unfair cop! Prison Cell 8447.

475
00:28:59,000 --> 00:29:01,640
Doctor!

476
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:03,840
The governor will see you now.

477
00:29:03,840 --> 00:29:06,960
Oh, good. Great. I think.

478
00:29:08,960 --> 00:29:13,720
Ooh. Hello, you're clearly an
android and I'm your new cellmate!

479
00:29:16,840 --> 00:29:20,120
You all right? It hurts!

480
00:29:20,120 --> 00:29:23,360
I'm the Doctor. Tell me the trouble.

481
00:29:25,920 --> 00:29:27,880
Interesting.

482
00:29:27,880 --> 00:29:30,240
You're the governor?
There's been a mistake.

483
00:29:30,240 --> 00:29:32,960
We don't make mistakes on Volag-Noc.
Safe!

484
00:29:32,960 --> 00:29:36,240
But my friend's been...

485
00:29:37,160 --> 00:29:40,440
Close. You were saying?

486
00:29:40,440 --> 00:29:45,480
I... Ah, yes, your "friend".

487
00:29:45,480 --> 00:29:49,040
We're still collating charges,
but he's been a very naughty boy.

488
00:29:49,040 --> 00:29:51,480
Minor traffic violations,
1,400 counts.

489
00:29:51,480 --> 00:29:55,120
Evading library fines, 250 counts.

490
00:29:55,120 --> 00:29:57,320
C'mon, that's nothing serious!

491
00:29:57,320 --> 00:29:59,120
Planetary demolition.

492
00:29:59,120 --> 00:30:02,640
How many counts? 17. No, 18.

493
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:07,320
Ouch. And all dating back...
3,000 years?!

494
00:30:07,320 --> 00:30:10,120
Well, I'm sure he had his reasons.

495
00:30:10,120 --> 00:30:13,200
Maybe, but these charges have
been extracted from his own brain.

496
00:30:13,200 --> 00:30:19,280
He knows what he's guilty of. And

497
00:30:13,200 --> 00:30:19,280
they've earned him... Let's see...
2 billion years in prison.

498
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:23,320
2 billion?! He really should have
taken back those library books.

499
00:30:23,320 --> 00:30:25,720
Hang on, there's more.

500
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:30,440
There's something here about a
"Doctor Vile", wanted for piracy.

501
00:30:30,440 --> 00:30:32,400
As well as his accomplice.

502
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:34,080
You!

503
00:30:41,360 --> 00:30:44,400
So anyway, Caw then said -
did I mention Caw before?

504
00:30:44,400 --> 00:30:50,720
Big, metal, bird, eats gold for
breakfast - anyway, he told us that
Baltazar is after the Infinite,

505
00:30:50,720 --> 00:30:54,360
the starship that has the
power to create your heart's desire.

506
00:30:54,360 --> 00:30:58,640
Baltazar - nasty flea, used to live
here. Anyway, we have to chase
around, stopping him...

507
00:30:58,640 --> 00:31:01,360
Ow! Oooh, sorry! Sorry.

508
00:31:01,360 --> 00:31:03,000
Hang on,

509
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:05,720
you've been inhibited! I have.

510
00:31:05,720 --> 00:31:09,160
You couldn't commit
a crime if you tried! I could not.

511
00:31:09,160 --> 00:31:12,080
you shouldn't be here at all!
Oh, I'm not having this.

512
00:31:14,160 --> 00:31:18,080
Thank you. Right, we'll have

513
00:31:14,160 --> 00:31:18,080
to dig our way out.

514
00:31:18,080 --> 00:31:22,640
Don't suppose you've concealed
a teaspoon? I lost mine.
There's a more direct way.

515
00:31:22,640 --> 00:31:24,760
Now.

516
00:31:25,600 --> 00:31:30,400
Oooh! What was that?

517
00:31:30,400 --> 00:31:32,520
Warder, what's up with the lights?

518
00:31:32,520 --> 00:31:36,760
Power fluctuation detected,
Governor.
A cell has been opened from within.

519
00:31:36,760 --> 00:31:42,960
Opened? Where? Cell 8447.
That cell is off limits.

520
00:31:42,960 --> 00:31:45,760
Didn't your tin pet there
put the Doctor in Cell 8447?

521
00:31:45,760 --> 00:31:49,640
No, I gave explicit orders no-one
was to be put in with the gover...

522
00:31:49,640 --> 00:31:52,040
The governor, were you gonna say?

523
00:31:52,040 --> 00:31:55,600
I saw the data chip in your safe!
If you're not the governor,
who are you?

524
00:31:55,600 --> 00:31:58,880
Don't you get it? He's escaped.

525
00:31:58,880 --> 00:32:00,640
Your friend's let him out!

526
00:32:00,640 --> 00:32:04,080
And we've only been here five
minutes! Nice one, Doctor.

527
00:32:07,480 --> 00:32:09,400
No.

528
00:32:15,880 --> 00:32:18,160
What's doing that?

529
00:32:18,160 --> 00:32:20,040
Locke.

530
00:32:21,480 --> 00:32:24,520
Hello, Martha Jones!
You'll never guess who I'm with!

531
00:32:24,520 --> 00:32:26,120
The real governor?

532
00:32:26,120 --> 00:32:30,800
Oh, you guessed! Thing is, if Locke
here is the governor, who are you?

533
00:32:30,800 --> 00:32:32,640
Warder!

534
00:32:34,640 --> 00:32:38,040
You don't know what you've done,
letting him out.

535
00:32:38,040 --> 00:32:40,360
Hang on, hold this for a moment,
will you?

536
00:32:40,360 --> 00:32:45,960
But there's nothing on it!

537
00:32:40,360 --> 00:32:45,960
It's psychic, and it tells me you're
"Constantine Ethelred Gurney.

538
00:32:45,960 --> 00:32:51,440
"Prisoner" Aha! Convicted of
blackmail, fraud...blah, blah, blah,
blah, blah, released... Released?!

539
00:32:51,440 --> 00:32:54,880
I did my time, I got let out,
I broke back in.

540
00:32:54,880 --> 00:32:57,520
That's new. Why?

541
00:32:57,520 --> 00:33:00,400
Because of him!
Living here in luxury.

542
00:33:00,400 --> 00:33:03,040
He's an android.
He doesn't even need it.

543
00:33:03,040 --> 00:33:06,200
But me, there are people
across the seven galaxies

544
00:33:06,200 --> 00:33:10,240
who still want my head on a plate,
putting my face on Wanted posters.

545
00:33:10,240 --> 00:33:13,480
"Wanted Dead or Alive"
open brackets, "preferably dead".

546
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:16,840
Close brackets. I get the picture.
There was this guy I met.

547
00:33:16,840 --> 00:33:19,520
Sold me a nifty little
program on the warders.

548
00:33:19,520 --> 00:33:21,600
They saw me as Locke,
and Locke as me.

549
00:33:21,600 --> 00:33:24,680
This "guy", name of Mergrass?

550
00:33:24,680 --> 00:33:26,800
You know him! Great guy.

551
00:33:26,800 --> 00:33:30,160
Anyway, I kept Locke safely
locked up, until you come along!

552
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:35,080
Free.

553
00:33:35,080 --> 00:33:37,440
At last, Gurney.

554
00:33:37,440 --> 00:33:39,400
Now now, Mr Locke, we had a deal.

555
00:33:39,400 --> 00:33:43,320
No deals. Creatures like Gurney
are beyond redemption.

556
00:33:43,320 --> 00:33:47,560
Their rehabilitation is pointless.

557
00:33:47,560 --> 00:33:52,360
Warder. All the prisoners in
Volag-Noc are beyond rehabilitation.

558
00:33:52,360 --> 00:33:54,240
They must die.

559
00:33:54,240 --> 00:33:56,040
Commencing cell sterilisation.

560
00:33:56,040 --> 00:33:59,600
On your command.

561
00:33:59,600 --> 00:34:02,520
You can't! Stop it!
Stop it now! It's not their fault.

562
00:34:02,520 --> 00:34:05,800
It's the only way to cure them.
Safe!

563
00:34:07,680 --> 00:34:10,280
It's the only way.

564
00:34:10,280 --> 00:34:12,880
It's the only way.

565
00:34:12,880 --> 00:34:16,240
Doctor, the prisoners! I'm on it.

566
00:34:16,240 --> 00:34:19,440
Gurney, how do we stop it? I need
that program Mergrass sold you

567
00:34:19,440 --> 00:34:24,000
so the Warders won't take Locke's
orders any more! Not my problem.

568
00:34:19,440 --> 00:34:24,000
I'm getting out of here!

569
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:28,000
The data chip! Gurney! Stop. Stop!

570
00:34:30,120 --> 00:34:32,480
Order terminated.

571
00:34:32,480 --> 00:34:34,640
Oh, yes! Skill.

572
00:34:34,640 --> 00:34:36,960
Now, where's my sonic screwdriver?

573
00:34:39,200 --> 00:34:42,240
Mind. You'll do yourself a damage.

574
00:34:47,640 --> 00:34:49,840
There's nowhere to run, Gurney!

575
00:34:49,840 --> 00:34:51,800
Got to get away from here.

576
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:54,360
Gurney?

577
00:34:54,360 --> 00:34:58,360
Gurney? Greener than a
seasick kitten, aren't you?

578
00:34:58,360 --> 00:35:02,200
Take me with you, in your ship!
I can't fly the TARDIS. Is that so?

579
00:35:02,200 --> 00:35:04,400
Then you're no use to me, are...

580
00:35:06,320 --> 00:35:08,160
It can't be.

581
00:35:08,160 --> 00:35:09,320
What?

582
00:35:10,640 --> 00:35:12,920
Revenge!

583
00:35:12,920 --> 00:35:14,360
Finally!

584
00:35:14,360 --> 00:35:17,320
Baltazar!

585
00:35:17,320 --> 00:35:19,680
The final data chip,

586
00:35:19,680 --> 00:35:22,160
at last! Gurney, no!

587
00:35:25,360 --> 00:35:27,120
Caw!

588
00:35:29,640 --> 00:35:32,520
Oh, no, you don't.

589
00:35:32,520 --> 00:35:36,800
Caw? Sorry, Miss Martha.

590
00:35:36,800 --> 00:35:41,040
Caw's been a dirty birdie.

591
00:35:41,040 --> 00:35:44,120
So you were working with him
all the time, weren't you?

592
00:35:44,120 --> 00:35:47,520
You sent us on this hunt
for the data chips, on his orders.

593
00:35:47,520 --> 00:35:49,040
I'm sorry.

594
00:35:49,040 --> 00:35:51,840
It's the gold, see.

595
00:35:51,840 --> 00:35:57,160
He promised me
all the gold I could eat.

596
00:35:57,160 --> 00:35:58,680
Caw!

597
00:35:59,720 --> 00:36:05,000
Gurney, he got me right
in the fusion chamber.

598
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:06,920
I'm done for now.

599
00:36:06,920 --> 00:36:09,160
There must be something I can do.

600
00:36:09,160 --> 00:36:11,200
There's not.

601
00:36:11,200 --> 00:36:15,920
Doctor! Doctor, we have to help him,
we have to do something please.

602
00:36:15,920 --> 00:36:18,240
Caw runs on gold fusion.

603
00:36:18,240 --> 00:36:21,240
Once his reactor's burned out,
that's it.

604
00:36:21,240 --> 00:36:23,480
Va...

605
00:36:23,480 --> 00:36:25,240
va...

606
00:36:25,240 --> 00:36:27,680
voom.

607
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:30,920
Caw?

608
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:32,600
Caw!

609
00:36:32,600 --> 00:36:37,120
Good afternoon, Doctor.
We have some unfinished business!

610
00:36:40,280 --> 00:36:43,160
Get in. Turn around.

611
00:36:43,160 --> 00:36:45,760
Hands in the air!
So, how'd you find us?

612
00:36:45,760 --> 00:36:49,280
It's very tricky to track a TARDIS.

613
00:36:45,760 --> 00:36:49,280
I had insider information.

614
00:36:49,280 --> 00:36:52,840
Have you met Squawk? My brooch!

615
00:36:52,840 --> 00:36:54,800
Aw, no.

616
00:36:54,800 --> 00:36:59,640
This little accessory has helped
me track you every step of the way.

617
00:36:59,640 --> 00:37:02,160
Fly away, birdie.

618
00:37:02,160 --> 00:37:06,360
Squawk! An accessory to murder.
Surely that's you, Doctor?

619
00:37:06,360 --> 00:37:09,880
You needed a little bit of help,
collecting the data chips.

620
00:37:09,880 --> 00:37:14,000
I knew my poor old cellmates,
who told me all about the Infinite,

621
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:16,040
would never willingly
give you theirs.

622
00:37:16,040 --> 00:37:18,360
First, there was Kaliko.

623
00:37:20,320 --> 00:37:24,640
Then, there was Mergrass.
Now, he dried up very quickly.

624
00:37:28,680 --> 00:37:32,560
And that was Gurney's. Pick it up.

625
00:37:32,560 --> 00:37:34,840
This is why you needed me, isn't it?

626
00:37:34,840 --> 00:37:38,480
You knew only my TARDIS could track
each data chip from planet to planet.

627
00:37:38,480 --> 00:37:44,040
I knew only you'd have something
that could read data chips older

628
00:37:38,480 --> 00:37:44,040
than recorded history itself.

629
00:37:44,040 --> 00:37:45,720
Off you go.

630
00:37:56,520 --> 00:37:59,000
The Hesperus Galaxy.

631
00:37:59,000 --> 00:38:01,640
Next.

632
00:38:01,640 --> 00:38:04,080
And that'll be the Ceres system.

633
00:38:04,080 --> 00:38:07,400
It's a map! Telling us the location
of the Infinite.

634
00:38:07,400 --> 00:38:09,920
Keep going.

635
00:38:09,920 --> 00:38:12,120
I spy...

636
00:38:12,120 --> 00:38:16,680
asteroid seven five seven four...
B? Yeah, B.

637
00:38:16,680 --> 00:38:18,760
Set your controls. We're going.

638
00:38:18,760 --> 00:38:24,160
This isn't a taxi! Set the controls,

639
00:38:18,760 --> 00:38:24,160
or Miss Martha gets skewered.

640
00:38:24,160 --> 00:38:28,840
Look, Baltazar, the Infinite -
it's a myth, a legend.

641
00:38:28,840 --> 00:38:35,920
But even if it does exist, even if
it contains a fraction of the power
everyone claims, it'll consume you.

642
00:38:35,920 --> 00:38:41,440
Destroy you! No, it'll give
me my heart's desire, Doctor.

643
00:38:41,440 --> 00:38:44,200
So set the controls.

644
00:38:50,360 --> 00:38:52,320
That's the course laid in?

645
00:38:52,320 --> 00:38:55,160
Yes. And all you have to do
is push the button?

646
00:38:55,160 --> 00:38:59,040
Well, more or less. Then I
don't need you any more, do I?

647
00:38:59,040 --> 00:39:02,920
Er... No! Doctor!

648
00:39:12,320 --> 00:39:15,080
Martha?

649
00:39:17,160 --> 00:39:18,880
No!

650
00:39:18,880 --> 00:39:20,400
Martha!

651
00:39:20,400 --> 00:39:21,920
MARTHA!

652
00:39:25,320 --> 00:39:27,920
He'll be back.

653
00:39:27,920 --> 00:39:32,280
He's a thousand light years away,
alone in the cold.

654
00:39:32,280 --> 00:39:35,520
We won't be seeing him again
for a while,

655
00:39:35,520 --> 00:39:38,720
not before I get
my heart's desire anyway.

656
00:39:48,080 --> 00:39:50,120
She's huge.

657
00:39:50,120 --> 00:39:52,680
The wreck of the Infinite.

658
00:39:52,680 --> 00:39:54,640
At last.

659
00:39:57,560 --> 00:40:00,360
She was smashed to bits
centuries back.

660
00:40:00,360 --> 00:40:03,320
Flotsam spread out
over half the galaxy.

661
00:40:03,320 --> 00:40:09,840
Found out on Volag-Noc that Kaliko,
Mergrass and Gurney had all come

662
00:40:03,320 --> 00:40:09,840
by bits of the flight recorder.

663
00:40:09,840 --> 00:40:13,240
Aw, and they wouldn't
share them with you?!

664
00:40:13,240 --> 00:40:14,880
Not even with each other.

665
00:40:14,880 --> 00:40:17,320
I guess X marks the spot?

666
00:40:17,320 --> 00:40:19,040
In you go.

667
00:40:27,800 --> 00:40:29,800
You're looking for the hold.

668
00:40:29,800 --> 00:40:33,200
The hold? Won't that be... Aah!

669
00:40:33,200 --> 00:40:35,480
Down, yup.

670
00:40:39,440 --> 00:40:42,480
Diagnosis: no bones broken.

671
00:40:42,480 --> 00:40:44,840
Well, that's something.

672
00:40:44,840 --> 00:40:46,720
Hello?

673
00:40:47,640 --> 00:40:49,440
Hello?

674
00:40:49,440 --> 00:40:51,080
Hello.

675
00:40:51,080 --> 00:40:52,360
Doctor!

676
00:40:52,360 --> 00:40:55,480
I knew it! I knew you'd be back!

677
00:40:55,480 --> 00:40:58,320
Wait a minute, how?

678
00:41:02,080 --> 00:41:03,680
Girl?

679
00:41:05,200 --> 00:41:07,320
Girly?

680
00:41:08,320 --> 00:41:09,760
Martha?

681
00:41:09,760 --> 00:41:12,520
Watch out below!

682
00:41:12,520 --> 00:41:16,680
What? Ahoy there! Meet Squawk!

683
00:41:16,680 --> 00:41:20,400
All grown up now! Squawk!

684
00:41:24,640 --> 00:41:29,320
We haven't... We haven't quite
got the hang of landing yet!

685
00:41:35,520 --> 00:41:37,160
Doctor?

686
00:41:37,160 --> 00:41:40,320
Out for the count, Squawk!

687
00:41:40,320 --> 00:41:42,480
And I thought I could
rely on you, at least.

688
00:41:42,480 --> 00:41:45,560
Doctor says you're a bad influence,
like y'were on me Dad!

689
00:41:45,560 --> 00:41:47,680
And now I've exactly what you need.

690
00:41:47,680 --> 00:41:52,440
Gold. Lots and lots
of lovely, glittering gold.

691
00:41:52,440 --> 00:41:54,280
Keep you fed for years.

692
00:41:54,280 --> 00:41:55,840
Squawk!

693
00:41:58,200 --> 00:42:01,840
Oi! What do I keep on telling you?
Don't listen to the villains!

694
00:42:01,840 --> 00:42:05,800
That hurt.

695
00:42:05,800 --> 00:42:08,720
Where is she? Where's Martha?

696
00:42:10,640 --> 00:42:12,440
But what about the treasure?

697
00:42:12,440 --> 00:42:14,440
The heart's desire.

698
00:42:16,840 --> 00:42:18,600
Of course.

699
00:42:18,600 --> 00:42:20,160
You're not the Doctor.

700
00:42:20,160 --> 00:42:22,280
My heart's desire indeed.

701
00:42:26,600 --> 00:42:29,360
Now you have it.

702
00:42:29,360 --> 00:42:33,400
No. No! Nooo!

703
00:42:34,480 --> 00:42:38,000
Excuse me, I think that's
my friend you're scaring.

704
00:42:38,000 --> 00:42:40,200
Hiya! Can you make him go away?

705
00:42:40,200 --> 00:42:42,800
That's up to you, I'm afraid.
You conjured him up.

706
00:42:42,800 --> 00:42:45,200
But how am I supposed to...?

707
00:42:45,200 --> 00:42:49,280
Heart's desire.
I don't believe I walked into this.

708
00:42:49,280 --> 00:42:53,320
Gotcha! I said
"I don't believe this!"

709
00:42:55,040 --> 00:42:56,520
Oh, yes!

710
00:42:58,640 --> 00:43:03,280
Oh, don't even try to
find my heart's desire.

711
00:43:03,280 --> 00:43:05,360
Hello, you.

712
00:43:05,360 --> 00:43:08,120
Proper you.

713
00:43:08,120 --> 00:43:11,840
Aren't you gonna ask how I got here?
And about my adventures on Volag-Noc?

714
00:43:11,840 --> 00:43:15,960
I bottle-fed Squawk with molten gold
and reprogrammed Locke to run
a better prison?

715
00:43:15,960 --> 00:43:20,440
It's been three years, you know.
Three years?
Well, two and three-quarters.

716
00:43:20,440 --> 00:43:23,120
Regained a bit by flying
past light speed.

717
00:43:23,120 --> 00:43:26,600
Light speed? How?

718
00:43:23,120 --> 00:43:26,600
I gave Squawk's engine a bit of pep.

719
00:43:26,600 --> 00:43:29,000
Bit of zing. Bit of... Va-va-voom!

720
00:43:29,000 --> 00:43:31,240
Yeah. I knew you'd be back.

721
00:43:31,240 --> 00:43:34,000
So, this is the Infinite.

722
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:38,520
Every pirate and freebooter
and treasure-hunter dreams

723
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:38,520
of being the one to find this.

724
00:43:38,520 --> 00:43:40,680
Their heart's desire.

725
00:43:40,680 --> 00:43:43,160
What did it show you, by the way?

726
00:43:43,160 --> 00:43:46,680
Doesn't matter. Didn't work on me.

727
00:43:46,680 --> 00:43:49,880
Anyway, whatever power this place
had is fading away daily.

728
00:43:49,880 --> 00:43:54,160
Whole ship's held together
by wishes and hopes.
There's nothing living here?

729
00:43:54,160 --> 00:44:00,400
Not now. One of the Great Old
Ones was once. It died out here,
alone and lost.

730
00:44:00,400 --> 00:44:05,480
Screaming its rage and fury
into the solitude
until its unique power dissipated.

731
00:44:05,480 --> 00:44:08,320
Just left a little fading echo,

732
00:44:08,320 --> 00:44:11,200
enough to give us a glimpse
of our heart's desires.

733
00:44:12,400 --> 00:44:15,600
LAUGHTER

734
00:44:15,600 --> 00:44:18,600
Oh, no. Gold!

735
00:44:18,600 --> 00:44:23,840
Diamonds! Treasure, Doctor, enough
treasure to buy me a new ship.

736
00:44:23,840 --> 00:44:30,720
A whole fleet,
and I can destroy you, Earth,
Volag-Noc and everything in between.

737
00:44:30,720 --> 00:44:34,040
Be scourge of the Galaxy again?
Is that the best you can think of?

738
00:44:34,040 --> 00:44:36,640
It's not real.
It's just an echo of the power.

739
00:44:36,640 --> 00:44:38,640
He's not listening, Martha.

740
00:44:38,640 --> 00:44:44,240
Ship's so old and rusted, just
held together by wishful thinking.

741
00:44:44,240 --> 00:44:45,760
What?

742
00:44:53,520 --> 00:44:55,520
Come on, Captain Useless.

743
00:45:13,880 --> 00:45:17,840
Sorry, full up. There'll be
another one along in a minute.

744
00:45:17,840 --> 00:45:20,240
No! Doctor, you can't leave me here!

745
00:45:27,000 --> 00:45:30,280
I know he was rotten
to the core, but still...

746
00:45:30,280 --> 00:45:32,240
Oh, I left him a way out.

747
00:45:32,240 --> 00:45:33,680
Whoah!

748
00:45:34,520 --> 00:45:36,040
Squawk!

749
00:45:36,040 --> 00:45:42,440
Course, it'd only matter if
I didn't know exactly where Squawk
was gonna drop him off.

750
00:45:42,440 --> 00:45:44,480
Curse you, Doctor! Curse you!

751
00:45:47,520 --> 00:45:49,840
Searching for your heart's desire,
Martha.

752
00:45:49,840 --> 00:45:51,680
Never been all it's cracked up to be.

753
00:45:51,680 --> 00:45:54,920
Now, then, Martha Jones.

754
00:45:54,920 --> 00:45:57,200
Another job for you. Oh, yes? Yes.

755
00:45:57,200 --> 00:45:59,720
Start giving me some random numbers.

756
00:45:59,720 --> 00:46:02,400
Oh, not again.
Come on, it'll be fun!

757
00:46:02,400 --> 00:46:06,240
When have I ever let you down?
Ha ha ha ha!

